	(186,3,'2014-08-05 08:27:24','2014-08-05 08:27:24','<span style=\"color: #333333;\">This site was generously designed and developed by Matthew and Arlene Santos, Owners of\r\n<a title=\"Bay Area Web Design - AG Design Group\" href=\"http://www.agdesigngroup.com/\" target=\"_blank\">AG Design Group, Inc</a>., an award winning, full service Creative Marketing and Project Management Consultancy.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #333333;\">Matt and Arlene’s involvement with the Ronald McDonald House of San Francisco started with a Family Meal they volunteered for in 2003, as college students at USF.  They continued to support the House over the years by Naming the House in their United Way campaign and company matching gift program, and in recent years as Gold or Platinum Gala Sponsors.</span>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">In 2014 they offered to further support the House by offering an in-kind donation of a full, end-to-end, website redesign and development of the Ronald McDonald House of San Francisco’s website, featuring:</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #333333;\"> -   A new, up-to-date look and better user information flow</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #333333;\"> -   Easy to use content management system</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #333333;\"> -   Social Media and Rich Media features and integration</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #333333;\"> -   A Mobile Optimized website that is accessible from various mobile devices</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>“The website has been a labor of love. Our job was to re-design the frontend with adherence to the Ronald McDonald House brand guidelines, re-architect the functionality, and translate this over to mobile.  We re-engineer the flow, layout, and experience of the site, in order to bring the website to life. Our hope is that the new website brings more traffic and attention to the House’s cause, increases donor response, and is a launching pad for charity events and a showcase for all the great work and services the House and it’s staff provides.\"</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>- <a title=\"Arlene Santos - AG Design Group - Walnut Creek Web Design\" href=\"http://www.agdesigngroup.com/our-team/arlene-santos/\" target=\"_blank\">Arlene Santos</a>, CEO of <a title=\"AG Design Group Web Design\" href=\"http://www.agdesigngroup.com/\" target=\"_blank\">AG Design Group</a></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>“We couldn’t think of a more deserving organization than the Ronald McDonald House of San Francisco. It was a true pleasure working with them to create something special.  In order to make the website truly usable, users need to be able to access and use the website from their mobile devices. With responsive design technology, the website is automatically sized and scaled to each mobile device and tablet. People are increasingly viewing the Internet on their phones and tablets; so it is important that users be able view and utilize the site as it was intended to be.  By furthering the online presence across all mobile platforms, our hope is to increase viewership, conversation, and donations. We hope the new site gives a little boost to the many great things to come.”</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>- <a title=\"Matt Santos - AG Design Group - Bay Area Web Design\" href=\"http://www.agdesigngroup.com/our-team/matt-santos/\" target=\"_blank\">Matt Santos</a>, COO of <a title=\"AG Design Group - Bay Area Web Design\" href=\"http://www.agdesigngroup.com/about-agd/\" target=\"_blank\">AG Design Group</a></em></p>\r\n\r\n<address><a href=\"http://rmh.dev/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/santos1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-208\" src=\"http://rmh.dev/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/santos1-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"santos\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" /></a></address>','Website Credits','','publish','open','open','','website-credits','','','2014-08-05 09:14:00','2014-08-05 09:14:00',